[asy]
pen sm=fontsize(9);
pair A=(3,7), B=(3,5), C=(-1,1), D=(-1,3), E=(3,1);
draw(A--B--C--D--cycle);
draw(B--E--C, dotted);
label("$A(3,7)$", A, NE, sm);
label("$B(3,5)$", B, E, sm);
label("$E(3,1)$", E, SE, sm);
label("$C(-1,1)$", C, SW, sm);
label("$D(-1,3)$", D, NW, sm);
label("$4$", (C+E)/2, S, sm);
label("$2$", (C+D)/2, W, sm);
draw(rightanglemark(B,E,C));
[/asy]

The length of $CD$ is $2$, and the length of $CE$ is $4$, so the area of parallelogram $ABCD$ is $2\cdot4 = \boxed{8}$.

